Quarky.py¶

Main entry point for the Quarky application.

This module initializes the GUI, handles application-level logic, and manages interactions between different components.

scripts.ExperimentThread module¶

class scripts.ExperimentThread.ExperimentThread(config, soccfg, exp, soc, parent=None)¶

Bases: QObject

This class is used to run an RFSOC experiment, meant to be used on a separate QThread than the main loop. The point is that running an RFSOC experiment will take a very long time, and we don’t want to lock up the UI while that’s going on. The intended usage is for an ExterimentThread object to be created, moved to a new QThread, then run. It will then communicate with the main program via signals, as intended in Qt, making it thread-safe.
